Modifications (Apache-2.0 change notice)
----------------------------------------
This file (material-symbols-rounded.woff2) is a SUBSET of the upstream variable
font, produced with fontTools (pyftsubset). Only the icon glyphs used by the
Lessgo app-chrome UI are retained, plus the Latin alphabet/digits/underscore
glyphs required as ligature-input components. All four variation axes
(FILL, GRAD, opsz, wght) are preserved (no axis was pinned/instanced), so
`font-variation-settings: 'FILL' 1` still animates. The full ~5.3 MB upstream
font is intentionally NOT committed.

Regeneration
------------
The retained icon set is the ligature-name list in ./icons.txt (one name per
line). To regenerate after editing that list:

  python -m fontTools.subset <MaterialSymbolsRounded-full.woff2> \
    --output-file=material-symbols-rounded.woff2 \
    --flavor=woff2 --no-layout-closure --layout-features='rlig,rclt,liga,calt' \
    --glyphs-file=<icon-names-that-are-glyph-names> \
    --text='abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789_'

(--no-layout-closure is required: without it the shared Latin alphabet pulls in
every icon via ligature closure, bloating the output back to multi-MB.)

